title: [Temple Burrow, Koar and Cholen]
description: Koar Street ends in a huge hill of ice that serves as part of the town wall.  Priests representing several orders come and go through a tunnel in the ice, or stand talking quietly, carefully polishing symbols of their deities.

Koar Street ends in a huge hill of ice that serves as part of the town wall.  The only light in the area flows through an unobtrusive tunnel in the ice.  The sound of chanting can be heard from somewhere deep within the hill.
